## Checklist for New Components

### Responsive Design

- [ ] Uses `mx-auto` with appropriate `max-w-*` for centering
- [ ] Has progressive horizontal padding: `px-4 sm:px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-[80px]`
- [ ] Typography scales responsively across breakpoints
- [ ] Spacing uses responsive values: `gap-[X] md:gap-[Y] lg:gap-[Z]`
- [ ] Layout adapts from mobile (stacked) to desktop (horizontal)
- [ ] Images and icons scale appropriately
- [ ] Consistent with existing page components

### SEO and Accessibility

- [ ] Uses semantic HTML elements (`<section>`, `<main>`, `<nav>`, etc.)
- [ ] Has proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3, no skipped levels)
- [ ] All images have descriptive `alt` text
- [ ] Interactive elements have appropriate ARIA labels
- [ ] All content is keyboard accessible
- [ ] Form inputs have associated labels
- [ ] Page structure uses proper HTML5 landmarks
